As I believe I already pointed out, they are exactly opposed to the judeo-xian self-repressive denial of human nature.  Is it natural for priests to be celibate?  Is it natural to turn the other cheek when struck?  Is it natural for people to feel guilty over a basic attraction to another?  Is it natural for people to want to kill, then outlaw it, and still do it in the name of some “higher” purpose anyway?  <br>
<br>
No.<br>
<br>
Here is the rub.  Any satanist you walk up to and ask will tell you almost nothing.  They will say, “Go buy a copy of The Satanic Bible by Anton LeVey and read it.”  Then maybe Satan Speaks, or The Satanic Rituals.  If you have more questions they really aren’t interested in helping you.  They aren’t some sideshow to be gawked at.  You either read and understand, or you don’t.  They aren’t looking to win converts.  If you don’t fit, that’s fine with them, move along…<br>
<br>
Go to one of their <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.personalsatan.com/lttd/ubbthreads.php?Cat=" target="top">web boards</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and log on.  You won’t see anything until you create an account, but if your salvation is so weakly held that the reading of some 36 year old book will shake you from it, then I have to laugh.  As one Magister put it, “Fear controls the herds, be not afraid.”<br>
<br>
From Joshua, a Church of Satan member:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>These are only my observations, and I want it to be clear that I am not speaking with any authority other than my own limited experience and superior intelligence (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). That caveat thus given, I now present my modest little FAQ for the scrutiny of the board members as well as the erudition of the newbies: <br>
<br>
(I welcome any suggestions, criticisms, or additions) <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1. Children are naturally Satanic / natural Satanists.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
This error arises from misreading the section of The Satanic Bible that discusses imagery in Satanic magic. Children are natural magicians, but magician does not equal Satanist. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2. Satanists hate Christians.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
This one can be especially irritating to hear over and over again. While Satanists do reject the whole of Christian philosophy as the anti-human and anti-self dogma that it is, the adherants to Christian philosophy are accepted as just another herd group that can be manipulated to further the Satanist's agenda. There is nothing special about Christianity that sets it apart from the Democratic Party, rock groupies, political demonstrators, or any other group-identity fanatics as far as the Satanist is concerned. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3. There are different sects within Satanism</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Wrong. There is only Satanism as codified and defined by Anton LaVey in The Satanic Bible. The only institution that remains steadfastly true to this philosophy is the church that Doktor LaVey himself founded -- the Church of Satan. All other institutions (including their members) that claim the title of &quot;Satanist&quot; are pseudosatanists or Devil worshippers. <br>
<br>
Despite claims to the contrary, the vast majority of these pretenders could never function as a Satanist (because, quite simply, they are not Satanists) and eventually wind up in jail or back in church where they belong. This truth will become more and more apparent as an individual's understanding of real Satanism grows. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>4. Satanism is all about doing whatever you like.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
This requires clarification. Indulgence is indeed the main aspect of Satanism, but it is not the only one. The goal of the Satanist is not to engage in mindless gratification, but rather to achieve &quot;strength through joy.&quot; It is about recognizing the absolute sovereignty of the ego and the methods to utilize one's being as a tool for achieving joy and self-aggrandizement. It is not about smoking dope, getting shitfaced, or any other temporarilly gratifying activities that, ultimately, lead to nowhere. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>5. Satanism is inclusive to all who accept themselves and reality.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Satanism is not a religion for stoners, morons, group-huggers, lonely misfits, criminals, or other non-functioning members of society. Whether they accept themselves or not, they will never be able to utilize Satanic methods for self-aggrandizement. It is good if they know their place, and that place is not here. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>6. You don't have to agree with all of The Satanic Bible to consider yourself a Satanist.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
First of all, it isn't about &quot;agreement&quot; or acquiescence; it is about resonance. Satanism is a religion for the individual -- that's true -- but it must be understood that it is NOT for just any old &quot;individual&quot;; it is for Satanic individuals. <br>
<br>
So how do you know if you are a Satanic individual? If you can read The Satanic Bible and find that its words resonate with your understanding of the world, if you are willing to personally verify the assertions and methodologies outlined therein, if you find it (all of it) to be a gratifying and workable philosophy -- then you know that you are a Satanic individual. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>7. Satanists aren't REALLY &quot;born,&quot; they are made.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
Those who make this statement are usually shit-disturbers or non-Satanists desperately trying to &quot;convert&quot; or &quot;fit in&quot; (which belies a complete ignorance of what is meant by divorcing oneself from hypocritical self-deceit). But for those who don't &quot;get it,&quot; I'll use a simile: &quot;Geniuses are born, not made.&quot; You can study something to find out if you're good at it, or even learn by rote if you're not good at it, but you will never attain the level of mastery that a genius has in that particular field. They just have a knack for it. They were born that way. <br>
<br>
Similarly, Real Satanists have a &quot;knack&quot; for Satanism in a way that simply cannot be learned. They don't &quot;follow&quot; the rules or live by the &quot;word&quot; because their religion &quot;tells them to.&quot; They live this way because, for the way they inherently are, it is the most gratifying and natural existence for them. They just have a knack for it. They were born that way. <br>
<br>
So one might ask of himself, &quot;Am I a Satanic Genius?&quot; <br>
<br>
Which is really the same as asking, &quot;Am I a Satanist?&quot; <br>
<br>
Remember -- &quot;hypocritical self-deceit&quot; applies to non-Satanists who try to be a Satanist.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I will not presume to speak further on their behalf.  Go to their site, read it and understand if you want to talk about it further.  Otherwise shut up about the stereo types your church would have you spew.  You don't even know anyone well enough for them to tell you they are a Satanist, and I am sick of the garbage that is being falsely spread about them.  The world has enough small minded prejudices in it already. <p>DBC67<br>
